  "prompt": "Why do people get cranky when they don't eat?",
  "response": "People get cranky when they don't eat due to several physiological and psychological reasons:\n\n1. Low Blood Sugar (Hypoglycemia)\n- Decreases energy levels\n- Triggers stress hormones like cortisol and adrenaline\n- Causes irritability and mood changes\n\n2. Hunger Hormones\n- Ghrelin (hunger hormone) increases\n- Causes feelings of discomfort and agitation\n- Can lead to decreased patience and increased negative emotions\n\n3. Brain Chemistry Changes\n- Reduced glucose affects brain function\n- Decreases serotonin and dopamine levels\n- Impacts mood regulation and emotional control\n\n4. Energy Depletion\n- Body lacks necessary nutrients\n- Leads to fatigue and decreased cognitive function\n- Reduces ability to manage stress and emotions\n\n5. Evolutionary Response\n- Hunger historically signaled potential survival threat\n- Triggers heightened alertness and defensive behaviors\n- Promotes aggressive responses to secure food\n\nThis phenomenon is often colloquially referred to as being \"hangry\" - a combination of hungry and angry. Eating regular, balanced meals helps maintain stable blood sugar and mood.",
